caption.title: Temporal distribution and frequency of dengue reports in the states and federal district of Brazil, 1990–2017.
caption.p: *Abbreviations correspond to the Brazilian states and Federal District. AC—Acre; AL—Alagoas; AP—Amapá; AM—Amazonas; BA—Bahia; CE—Ceará; DF—Distrito Federal; ES—Espírito Santo; GO—Goiás; MA—Maranhão; MT—Mato Grosso; MS—Mato Grosso do Sul; MG—Minas Gerais; PA—Pará; PB—Paraíba; PR—Paraná; PE—Pernambuco; PI—Piauí; RR—Roraima; RO—Rondônia; RJ—Rio de Janeiro; RN—Rio Grande do Norte; RS—Rio Grande do Sul; SC—Santa Catarina; SP—São Paulo; SE—Sergipe; TO–Tocantins.
